Usage Instructions
Prepare the dockerfile Directory:

Each subdirectory under dockerfile (e.g., dockerfile/frontend) should contain:
A Dockerfile with the build instructions.
All required files (source code, JARs, configuration files).
Run the Workflow:

Build Docker Images Locally:
bash
Copy code
make build
Initialize and Apply Terraform:
bash
Copy code
make terraform-init
make terraform-apply
Deploy Kubernetes Resources:
bash
Copy code
make k8s-apply
Start the Entire Flow:
bash
Copy code
make start
Stop and Clean Up:
bash
Copy code
make stop
Verify Deployment:

Use kubectl get pods -n app to check that the pods are running.
Use kubectl get services -n app to verify service endpoints.